when the 'userSave' event is fired, all sources save based on the id stored in core.userData.documents[core.currentDocID].saveSources[saveSourceName].

To check if a document exists, check whether core.userData.documents[core.currentDocID] has any data.

To initialise a save source, set core.userData.documents[core.currentDocID].saveSources[source] = core.currentDocID.
The save source should then take on this and do something with it, e.g. hash it or otherwise.